<H2>Copyright Tab</H2>
<P>This screen contains the licence field from the control record and the text of the copyright record.</P>
<TABLE>
  <TR>
    <TH>Field</TH><TH>Description</TH>
  </TR>
  <TR>
    <TD>Licence</TD>
    <TD>This is the licence the package is released under. It can be Free or Non Free. Free is defined as a package that meets the Open Source definition available at
       <A HREF="http://www.opensource.org/docs/osd">http://www.opensource.org/docs/osd</A>.
       <BR>Common licences that are classified as free include:
       <UL>
         <LI>Apache License, 2.0</LI>
         <LI>New and Simplified BSD licenses</LI>
         <LI>Boost Software License (BSL1.0)</LI>
         <LI>European Union Public License</LI>
         <LI>GNU General Public License (GPL)</LI>
         <LI>GNU General Public License version 3.0 (GPLv3)</LI>
         <LI>GNU Library or "Lesser" General Public License (LGPL)</LI>
         <LI>GNU Library or "Lesser" General Public License version 3.0 (LGPLv3)</LI>
         <LI>MIT license</LI>
         <LI>Mozilla Public License 1.1 (MPL)</LI>
         <LI>zlib/libpng license</LI>
       </UL>
       A Full list of currently approved free licences can be found at
       <A HREF="http://www.opensource.org/licenses">http://www.opensource.org/licenses</A>.
    </TD>
  <TR>
    <TD>Copyright</TD>
    <TD>The copyright text for the package. This is required. It must  contain the following information:
      <UL>
        <LI>the name of the upstream author(s)</LI>
        <LI>the names of current and past package maintainers</LI>
	<LI>the provenance of the upstream sources</LI>
	<LI>a verbatim copy of the copyright notice and distribution licence</LI>
      </UL>
    </TD>
  </TR>
</TABLE>

